<paragraph blockId="3.[151,480,1015,1042]" box="[151,480,1015,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,480,1015,1042]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,480,1015,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" box="[207,301,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leloii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,301,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. leloii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1086,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,312,1086,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leloii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,312,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Agrisius leloii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[324,418,1086,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,418,1086,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,559,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[235,1374,268,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,267,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Agrisius spp.: adults. 1, A. japonicus japonicus, ♂, Japan (©NHMUK); 2, A. japonicus japonicus, hOlOtype ♀, Japan (©NHMUK); 3, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♂, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 4, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♀, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 5, A. japonicus dubatolovi, holotype ♂, Thailand (after Orhant 2012); 6, A. japonicus dubatolovi, ♂, N VietnaM (SZMN); 7, A. orhanti, holotype ♂, S Laos (©NHMUK); 8, A. orhanti, paratype ♀, S Laos (CAV); 9, A. leloii, holotype ♂, C Vietnam (©NHMUK); 10, A. leloii, paratype ♀, C VietnaM (CAV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458418/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) is very close to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[816,960,1087,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[816,960,1087,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1249,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[235,1374,268,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,267,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Agrisius spp.: adults. 1, A. japonicus japonicus, ♂, Japan (©NHMUK); 2, A. japonicus japonicus, hOlOtype ♀, Japan (©NHMUK); 3, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♂, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 4, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♀, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 5, A. japonicus dubatolovi, holotype ♂, Thailand (after Orhant 2012); 6, A. japonicus dubatolovi, ♂, N VietnaM (SZMN); 7, A. orhanti, holotype ♂, S Laos (©NHMUK); 8, A. orhanti, paratype ♀, S Laos (CAV); 9, A. leloii, holotype ♂, C Vietnam (©NHMUK); 10, A. leloii, paratype ♀, C VietnaM (CAV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458418/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 1–8</figureCitation>
) by its external appearance, the long basal plate of the uncus with medial dorsal crest, the hood-like juxta, the absence of coremata on the apex of the valve (only longer hairs presented), the presence of only one, short saccular process, and the absence of cornuti and spinules in the aedeagus vesica, but the long distal branches of its uncus (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1343,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1420,201,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1428,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 21, A. japonicus japonicus, S KOrea, slide YK2801 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin; 22, A. japonicus albida, paratype, China, Jiangsu, slide AV1882; 23, A. japonicus dubatolovi, hOlOtype, Thailand (aFter Orhant 2012); 24, A. japonicus dubatolovi, N VietnaM, slide AV1690 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 25, A. orhanti, hOlOtype, S LaOs, slide AV3102; 26, A. leloii, paratype, C VietnaM, slide AV1777." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458424/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1356,1385,1195,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1429,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 27, A. leloii, hOlOtype, C VietnaM, slide AV1631 (©NHMUK); 28, A. guttivitta, C Nepal, slide AV1751 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 29, A. similis, China, Yunnan, slide AV1750 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 30, A. aestivalis, hOlOtype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1753 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 31, A. vernalis, hOlOtype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1752 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 32, A. excellens, hOlOtype, NE LaOs, slide YK2805 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">27</figureCitation>
) are very different from those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[524,666,1231,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[524,666,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[848,978,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1420,201,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1428,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 21, A. japonicus japonicus, S KOrea, slide YK2801 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin; 22, A. japonicus albida, paratype, China, Jiangsu, slide AV1882; 23, A. japonicus dubatolovi, hOlOtype, Thailand (aFter Orhant 2012); 24, A. japonicus dubatolovi, N VietnaM, slide AV1690 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 25, A. orhanti, hOlOtype, S LaOs, slide AV3102; 26, A. leloii, paratype, C VietnaM, slide AV1777." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458424/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 21–25</figureCitation>
) and resemble those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1855" box="[1301,1436,1231,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttivitta">
<emphasis box="[1301,1436,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. guttivitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[326,462,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[165,1429,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 27, A. leloii, hOlOtype, C VietnaM, slide AV1631 (©NHMUK); 28, A. guttivitta, C Nepal, slide AV1751 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 29, A. similis, China, Yunnan, slide AV1750 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 30, A. aestivalis, hOlOtype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1753 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 31, A. vernalis, hOlOtype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1752 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 32, A. excellens, hOlOtype, NE LaOs, slide YK2805 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458426/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 28–32</figureCitation>
). However, in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1855" box="[685,822,1267,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttivitta">
<emphasis box="[685,822,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. guttivitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group those branches are not curved dorsoventrally and are pointed apically, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" box="[670,759,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leloii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[670,759,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. leloii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[767,858,1302,1327]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[767,858,1302,1327]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the distal branches of the uncus have the short and trigonal apical-dorsal processes similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[766,907,1339,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[766,907,1339,1362]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, but differ from the latter by the claw-like apexes, which are curved downwards (in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[777,918,1375,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[777,918,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group they are curved upwards). The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" box="[370,459,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leloii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[370,459,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. leloii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[467,557,1410,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[467,557,1410,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[573,656,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–41" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[203,1409,193,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[172,1416,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33–41. Agrisius spp.: FeMale genitalia. 33, A. japonicus japonicus, Japan, slide AV1676; 34, A. japonicus albida, paratype, E China, slide AV1887; 35, A. orhanti, paratype, S LaOs, slide AV4314; 36, A. leloii, paratype, N VietnaM, slide AV1775; 37, A. guttivitta, Central Nepal, slide AV1677; 38, A. similis, N VietnaM, slide AV1669; 39, A. aestivalis, paratype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1708; 40, A. vernalis, paratype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1670; 41, A. excellens, paratype, NE LaOs, slide AV1675." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458428/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) differ from those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[943,1084,1411,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[943,1084,1411,1434]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[1263,1392,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–41" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[203,1409,193,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[172,1416,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33–41. Agrisius spp.: FeMale genitalia. 33, A. japonicus japonicus, Japan, slide AV1676; 34, A. japonicus albida, paratype, E China, slide AV1887; 35, A. orhanti, paratype, S LaOs, slide AV4314; 36, A. leloii, paratype, N VietnaM, slide AV1775; 37, A. guttivitta, Central Nepal, slide AV1677; 38, A. similis, N VietnaM, slide AV1669; 39, A. aestivalis, paratype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1708; 40, A. vernalis, paratype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1670; 41, A. excellens, paratype, NE LaOs, slide AV1675." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458428/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 33, 34</figureCitation>
) by the presence of a heavily sclerotized antevaginal plate, and from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1855" box="[916,1048,1447,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttivitta">
<emphasis box="[916,1048,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. guttivitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1353,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–41" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[203,1409,193,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[172,1416,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33–41. Agrisius spp.: FeMale genitalia. 33, A. japonicus japonicus, Japan, slide AV1676; 34, A. japonicus albida, paratype, E China, slide AV1887; 35, A. orhanti, paratype, S LaOs, slide AV4314; 36, A. leloii, paratype, N VietnaM, slide AV1775; 37, A. guttivitta, Central Nepal, slide AV1677; 38, A. similis, N VietnaM, slide AV1669; 39, A. aestivalis, paratype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1708; 40, A. vernalis, paratype, China, GuangdOng, slide AV1670; 41, A. excellens, paratype, NE LaOs, slide AV1675." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458428/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">Figs 37–41</figureCitation>
) by the absence of heavily sclerotized antrum. Taking into account all listed genitalic characters, we treat 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" box="[1250,1339,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leloii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1250,1339,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. leloii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,1482,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,1482,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
as a member of the separate species-group, which is morphologically intermediate between the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[1245,1387,1519,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1245,1387,1519,1542]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1855" box="[192,324,1555,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttivitta">
<emphasis box="[192,324,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="131">A. guttivitta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-groups.
</paragraph>
